.SH "NAME"
get_phy_device \- reads the specified PHY device and returns its \fIphy_device\fR struct
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'struct\ phy_device\ *\ get_phy_device('u
.BI "struct phy_device * get_phy_device(struct\ mii_bus\ *\ " "bus" ", int\ " "addr" ", bool\ " "is_c45" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIbus\fR
.RS 4
the target MII bus
.RE
.PP
\fIaddr\fR
.RS 4
PHY address on the MII bus
.RE
.PP
\fIis_c45\fR
.RS 4
If true the PHY uses the 802\&.3 clause 45 protocol
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Reads the ID registers of the PHY at
\fIaddr\fR
on the
\fIbus\fR, then allocates and returns the phy_device to represent it\&.
